  "prompt": "What is the ending of Game of Thrones?",
  "response": "The television series \"Game of Thrones,\" which aired its final episode on May 19, 2019, concluded with several significant events:\n\n1. **Bran Stark Becomes King**: Bran Stark is chosen as the new ruler of the Six Kingdoms (the North remains independent) after a council of Westeros' leaders decides to elect him based on his knowledge and wisdom as the Three-Eyed Raven.\n\n2. **Jon Snow's Fate**: Jon Snow, who kills Daenerys Targaryen to prevent her from further tyranny, is exiled to the Night's Watch. He ultimately reunites with the Free Folk beyond the Wall.\n\n3. **Sansa Stark Rules the North**: Sansa Stark declares the North as an independent kingdom and becomes its queen.\n\n4. **Arya Stark's Journey**: Arya Stark sets off on a voyage to explore unknown territories west of Westeros.\n\n5. **Tyrion Lannister's Role**: Tyrion Lannister is appointed as Bran's Hand of the King, tasked with rebuilding the kingdom.\n\nThe ending was met with mixed reactions from fans and critics, with some appreciating the closure of various character arcs while others were dissatisfied with the resolution of certain storylines.",
